fields.description:
While going through the manual steps in QA-737, it was noticed that when {{euare-accountlistpolicies}} was used to display an attached policy with the {{\-v/--verbose}} flag, the following would occur:
{code}
[root@g-12-12 ~]# euare-accountlistpolicies -p stack-limit --verbose -a engineering --region euca-admin@
euare-accountlistpolicies: error: missing access key ID; please supply one with -I
[root@g-12-12 ~]# euare-accountlistpolicies -p stack-limit -v -a engineering --region euca-admin@
euare-accountlistpolicies: error: missing access key ID; please supply one with -I
[root@g-12-12 ~]# euare-accountlistpolicies -v -a engineering --region euca-admin@
stack-limit
euare-accountlistpolicies: error: missing access key ID; please supply one with -I
{code}
Typically the {{\-v/--verbose}} flag will list the title of the policy along with the contents of the policy.
fields.summary: euare-accountlistpolicies -v/--verbose option fails to fetch contents of attached policies

comments.body: The output does not seem to include any debug output.  From the looks of it, you were simply missing credentials.  Would you please include a reproducer or more information?

Hey [~gholms],

I reproduced this.  I also added debugging output.  Let me know if you need any additional information.

[root@d-14 ~]# euare-accountcreate -a sales -w > .euca/sales-admin.ini
[root@d-14 ~]# euare-accountuploadpolicy -p cfn-stack-limit -a sales -f cfn-stack-limit.json

## After uploading the policy, tried different ways to display the contents ##

cfn-stack-limit
